Title: Claims-service response codes and status mapping
Date: 2026-02-05

Goal
Collect success and failure response bodies with HTTP status codes for claims-service
endpoints, and document where each response is generated in the code.

Scope
- Service: claims-service
- Base context path: /claims-service
- Controllers: ReimbursementProxyController
- Exception handling: claims-service GlobalExceptionHandler
- Security: SecurityConfig authenticationEntryPoint
- Shared response model: CommonResponse and ErrorResponse

Search details
1) Controllers and endpoints
   - File: services/claims-service/src/main/java/com/medgo/claims/controller/ReimbursementProxyController.java
   - Endpoints:
     * GET /api/v1/reimbursement/history
     * POST /api/v1/reimbursement/claimNature
     * POST /api/v1/reimbursement/bankMaster
     * POST /api/v1/reimbursement/viewAmountBreakDown
     * POST /api/v1/reimbursement/submit
     * POST /api/v1/reimbursement/resubmit

2) Exception handling (error responses with HTTP status codes)
   - File: services/claims-service/src/main/java/com/medgo/claims/exception/GlobalExceptionHandler.java
   - Mappings:
     * FeignException.NotFound -> 404
     * FeignException (non-404) -> downstream status
     * MemberCodeValidationException -> 403
     * JsonProcessingException -> 400
     * IllegalArgumentException -> 400
     * RuntimeException -> 500
     * Exception -> 500

3) Security unauthorized response
   - File: services/claims-service/src/main/java/com/medgo/claims/config/SecurityConfig.java
   - authenticationEntryPoint -> 401 with JSON body:
     {"error":"Unauthorized: Valid JWT token required. Please login first."}

4) Common response model used for success/error payloads
   - File: shared/common-objects/src/main/java/com/medgo/commons/CommonResponse.java
   - File: shared/common-objects/src/main/java/com/medgo/commons/ErrorResponse.java
   - Success example:
     {"statusCode":"200","response":"SUCCESS","data":{...},"traceId":"<traceId>"}
   - Error example:
     {"statusCode":"<status>","response":"ERROR","data":{"statusCode":<status>,"errorCode":null,"message":"...","errors":[]},"traceId":"<traceId>"}

